# Vantage Web Designs — Project Context

## What This Is
Agency website and base template for a web design business targeting SMBs.
This repo is copied and modified to create client site templates.

## Business Model
- **Subscription**: $150/mo — $0 down, hosting, unlimited edits, 24/7 support, analytics, 6-month minimum contract, site ownership transfers after 12 months
- **Lump sum**: $1,200 one-time + $25/mo hosting + $50/hr edits — client owns site outright
- **E-commerce**: Lump sum only, partner with Shopify dev
- Selling a relationship, not just a website
- Stripe payment links sent manually via email — no payment processing on site

## Template Strategy
- This repo = base template (agency site + starting point for all client builds)
- 3 initial templates: casual, professional, luxury
- Each template = copy of this repo with different CSS variables + section layouts
- Never reuse the same template in the same market
- `ui/` primitives are shared identically across all templates — only CSS vars and layouts change

## Stack
- Next.js 16.1.7 (App Router, Turbopack)
- Tailwind CSS v4 — utility classes only, no DaisyUI
- React Server Components by default — `'use client'` only when strictly needed
- `next/image` for all images, `next/font` for all fonts
- Static site — no auth, no database, no Stripe SDK
- Contact form via Web3Forms — no API route needed, submissions go directly to email inbox

## Contact Form Pattern (Web3Forms)
- Free at web3forms.com — 250 submissions/mo per account
- Each client gets their own free Web3Forms account and access key
- Access key stored in `.env.local` as `NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY`
- Key is safe to expose client-side — it only controls where emails are delivered
- Per-client `.env.local` vars:
  ```
  NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY=their_access_key
  NOTION_API_KEY=their_notion_key (if blog is active)
  NOTION_DATABASE_ID=their_database_id (if blog is active)
  ```

## Static Assets
- OG image and favicon MUST be in `public/` folder — not `src/styles/assets/`
- `public/preview.png` — 1200x630px OpenGraph image
- `public/favicon.png` — browser tab icon
- Images used in components (hero, etc.) live in `src/styles/assets/` and are imported via `next/image`

## Constants
All site-wide values live in `src/utils/constants.js`:
```js
export const BASE_URL = 'https://vantagewebdesigns.com';
export const SITE_NAME = 'Vantage Web Designs';
export const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'hello@vantagewebdesigns.com';
```
When copying for a client template, update all three values first.

## Blog
- Powered by Notion + `@notionhq/client` v4 + `notion-to-md`
- Blog is hidden from nav by default — add to `NAV_LINKS` in `Header.jsx` when ready
- Requires `NOTION_API_KEY` and `NOTION_DATABASE_ID` in `.env.local`

## What Was Removed from Original Boilerplate
- DaisyUI (replaced with custom component system)
- next-auth, mongodb, mongoose, @auth/mongodb-adapter
- Sign-in, Profile, auth API routes
- Stripe SDK, Stripe webhook route
- Tawk.to chat widget
- Old boilerplate env vars (MongoDB URI, NextAuth secret, Google OAuth, Resend, Stripe keys)
